  "prompt": "What is a bank branch name?",
  "response": "A bank branch name refers to a specific location or outlet of a bank. Each branch usually has a unique name that often incorporates the name of the bank along with a geographic identifier, which helps customers distinguish between different branches based on location. For example, a branch of \"First National Bank\" located in downtown Chicago might be called \"First National Bank \u2013 Chicago Downtown Branch.\" The branch name can be used in various contexts, such as in account statements, banking apps, and when providing address details for banking services.",
